{
  "texts": [
    "These model's performance in the human motion intention prediction is explained in this section.",
    "Performance of EEG/EMG signals on AH-CNN-LSTM and its advantagesThe collected EEG/EMG signals Sig In j are converted as spectrogram images by utilizing the technique named Short-Time Fourier Transform (STFT) 44.",
    "By leveraging this technique, each EEG/EMG signals are transformed into a 2D time-frequency matrix for obtaining the image-like representation.",
    "The STFT is estimated as follows.ST F T (y, u) = ∞ ∑ v=-∞ d (f).g [f -sJ].e -i 2πF uf Here, the input discrete signal is specified as d (f), and the window function is given as g [f] for the length P. Further, the total number of frequency bins is pointed as F, hop size is J and the variable ST F T (y, u) is the coefficient of the STFT for the y th time frame and u th frequency bin.",
    "Finally, the resultant spectrogram image is obtained and represented as Im spc b."
  ]
}